<br>
Any ideas? Anyone know who is the farthest along in SCFM? <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umezmoriah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mezmoriah</A> at: 12/26/01 2:02:54 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=maruku14>Maruku14</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/26/01 5:24:26 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> What is the final word on Spell Casting Fury Mastery???</span><hr size=1> A little while back, somebody gave a little info on what this skill did for them.  On one of their criticals, they got an extra two percent damage (4080 rather than 4000).<br>
<br>
I was personally expecting, in my characteristically pessimistic way, for the Mastery skill to raise the percentage chance for criticals to 8, 9, and 10 percent, which would be utterly laughable for the cost of six L59s, but not inconsistent with the other Wizard-specific abilities, all of which are pathetic.<br>
<br>
Of course, a _chance_ for an extra _two_ percent damage isn't even as &quot;good&quot; as my lowly prediction.  It's worse.<br>
<br>
Still, we obviously don't have the final word on this ability because people haven't been in the biggest hurry to spend hard-earned points on an obvious letdown.<br>
